  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya: Justice, Human Rights and Equality Engagement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve access to equitable formal and informal justice. 2) To increase capacity of justice seekers to claim their rights and access legal services. 3) To improve capacity of formal justice institutions to administer gender justice.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: the Judiciary, the National Legal Aid Service (NLAS), civil society organizations, community-based organizations, Court Users Committees, line ministries, informal justice sector actors, the Kenya National Council of Elders (KNCE), county governments.
Indirect beneficiaries: Justice seekers and vulnerable groups (women, girls and children).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to improve access to justice, reduce impunity and increase protection of constitutionally entrenched human rights.</narrative>
  </description>
